  "body": "seeing this:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/111600/70285307-6c10c780-180a-11ea-8253-c8e94e01eeca.png)\r\n\r\nmade me a bit worried and thinking.\r\nI do not think istanbul is contentious - I think it is just node operators not caring to update.\r\nPerhaps one idea to fight this problem in the future might be to degrade service when geth is not updated before a fork (perhaps with signaling on chain) - an Idea might be a X second sleep before answering a RPC call.\r\nI have seen this with libraries that also wanted to force users to update to newer versions.\r\nJust throwing the idea out there in the hope to spark a discussion - perhaps something arises from this.",
