    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Updating is a voluntary process. The devs can only ship a new code, but we cannot force people to update. This is a feature, not a bug.\r\n\r\nAlso I don't want to have control over when someone updates. If they decide to update 3 days before the fork, it's up to them, they know their business best. My best idea is to provide a means for auto-updating nodes (e.g. Ubuntu Snap), and describe to people how they can opt in if they wish so.\r\n\r\nEven then, updating still requires a reboot at some point, which we cannot decide for the user.",
